See I actually watch *and* understand basketball. Might wanna work on that other part.    Their are levels of talent in the NBA beyond just ‚Äústars‚Äù and ‚Äúrole players‚Äù. Mainly ‚Äúend of bench guys‚Äù.   The Lakers don‚Äôt really have many legitimate role players on their roster anymore. They traded most of that talent besides THT when they got Westbrook.   The ‚Äúrole players‚Äù LA has right now are more in the end-of-bench category outside of a couple. You can‚Äôt just put all the blame on them and assume they would step up to fill the hole in depth that Caruso and KCP left. That‚Äôs why Caruso is Caruso and KCP is KCP.    It‚Äôs like the Bucks during their first ten or so games‚Äî were scrubs like Justin Robinson and Sandro Mamukelashvili role players? No, they were high-end G League guys who had to pretend they were better than they actually were. And the Bucks lost a lot of those games as a result. Difference being Milwaukee just had to wait for guys to get healthy‚Äî LA‚Äôs roster just looks fundamentally lost.

You‚Äôd be surprised how many degenerates seem to feed on the suffering of others on the internet.   Btw, do you think the bucks would trade Sandro Mamukelashvili for Cade Bustingham and 2 firsts? That guy has never missed a three in his career whereas Cade has never made one.

Kalaitzakis had I think one decent game against the Mavericks, but overall was pretty uninspiring. He plays defense well-enough, rebounds and can make the occasional pass but that's about it.  > if I'm Bud, I'm treating this as an extra preseason game. Trot everyone to court and see if you have a hidden rotation guy buried in the bench.  That's exactly what's been happening the last 5-7 games. Justin Robinson is a two-way PG who was cut by the Thunder last year after 9 games. He's played as many minutes as Sengun. Sandro Mamukelashvili, a 54th pick on a two-way contract drafted to the defending champions has played more minutes than *19* first round picks. Bucks went into the season with an empty roster spot - which worked well last season since it meant they could get Teague and PJ - so the rotation is just so short right now that regardless of what Bud wants to do everyone is getting minutes.
I'm guessing George Hill/Pat Connaughton/Jordan Nwora/Thanasis Antetokounmpo/Bobby Portis. Portis is likely still on limited minutes, so yeah Sandro Mamukelashvili may see some bigger minutes.
